Class FileSystemEntityCapability

  • java.lang.Object

      • net.proteusframework.users.capability.AbstractDataCapability
        • net.proteusframework.users.capability.AbstractEntityCapability<FileSystemEntity>
          • net.proteusframework.data.filesystem.FileSystemEntityCapability
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Entity<Long>, net.proteusframework.users.capability.PrincipalGrantableCapability, net.proteusframework.users.capability.PrincipalGroupGrantableCapability

    @Entity
public class FileSystemEntityCapability
extends net.proteusframework.users.capability.AbstractEntityCapability<FileSystemEntity>
implements net.proteusframework.users.capability.PrincipalGroupGrantableCapability, net.proteusframework.users.capability.PrincipalGrantableCapability
    Capability to control access to files and directories. Will have EITHER a granted Principal or a granted PrincipalGroup. The subject is the FileSystemEntity being protected. A subject of null means the granted Principal or PrincipalGroup gets access to all FileSystemEntities. The operation (see AbstractDataCapability.getOperation() and FileSystemEntityCapabilityOperation determines what kind of access is being granted.
    Author:
    Greg Dick (gdick@i2rd.com)
